Reasoning: The paper deals with the degrees of freedom (DoF) regions of the two-user multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) broadcast channel with a general message set (BC-CM) under different channel state knowledge assumptions. This topic falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT) and network information theory (cs.ITP). The paper also addresses antenna configurations, which could fall under the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The study of DoF regions in MIMO systems is also related to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM).
